The paper discusses normalization techniques for deep neural networks, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The focus is on regularization through a new loss term that encourages stable variance of activations, which is relevant to topics such as optimization and regularization. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper discusses the separation of Gaussians, which is relevant to topics such as artificial intelligence and computer vision, suggesting cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) as possible sub-categories as well.
